{"type":"message","id":"3f9f2954","parentId":"22956223","timestamp":"2026-05-08T16:34:15.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why resetting doesn't leave 0 context remaining. They seem to be asking about how context window works after a reset.\n\nLooking at the numbers:\n- 88K/200K current context usage\n- If reset, the conversation context would be cleared but the window itself doesn't go to 0 - it's a fresh 200K window ready to be filled again.\n\nSo after reset, you'd have 200K available again, not 0. The context is cleared and you start fresh with a full 200K window.\n\nWait, I think they might be confused about the numbers. Let me re-read.\n\nThey said: \"ทำไมreset ละไม่เหลือ 0\" - \"Why after reset is it not 0 remaining?\"\n\n\nThey're thinking the remaining capacity should show as 0 after a reset, but that's not how it works. When you reset, the context window clears completely, giving you back the full 200K to work with. The capacity is always measured from the maximum window size, not from zero. Their calculation of 112K remaining (200K - 88K) was actually correct - that's the available space before the window fills up again.","thinkingSignature":"44d2fcd3a7887ef18794b5fb17a7adde833bcc26532aa5886bc4fcb2182a9b44"},{"type":"text","text":"เพราะ **context window** มันวัดจากขนาดสูงสุดของ window ครับ\n\n**ก่อน reset:**\n- ใช้ไป 88K / 200K\n- เหลือ 112K (200K - 88K)\n\n**หลัง reset:**\n- context ถูก clear หมด\n- window ว่างเปล่า เริ่มนับใหม่\n- พร้อมรับอีก **200K** เต็ม\n\nมันไม่ใช่ \"เหลือ 0\" แต่เป็น \"เริ่มต้นใหม่ที่ 200K\" ครับ 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":203,"output":460,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":34623,"totalTokens":35286,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778258041482,"responseId":"064d437bbf666105b6f927b085c55d59"}}
